<TEXT>
 authorities in new mexico say actor richard farnsworth has died of a
 self-inflicted gunshot wound.
 his fiancee says farnsworth, who had terminal cancer, was in incredible pain.
 earlier this year, he appeared at the academy awards.
 he was the oldest man to be nominated for best actor for his role in the 1999
 film, "the straight story."
 he also was nominated for "comes a horseman."
 farnsworth was a hollywood stuntman for 30 years before he began acting at the
 age of 57.
 richard farnsworth was 80.
